author: @snehasar3854
text:
I was reading a very sad story right now ... This song brightened up my mood... I love Seventeen and will always do... I always wished to have brothers like you all in real life... But I guess even if I can't meet you everyday or talk to you but you still always brought a sense of happiness and comfort in my life... You always make my day the brightest... I feel the sincere message everytime I listen to your music... I love you my brothers... As a single girl child I sometimes feel the need for a big bro... When other people talk about their siblings, l just feel a little jealous... But now that I have you all, not just one but THIRTEEN BIG BROS... I can proudly say that I have 13 brothers and my CARAT FAMILY to always comfort me, make me laugh and sometimes even cry because of their sincere feelings...My 13 Diamond Brothers... I love you~ 
Thank you for helping me in my hard times... Seranghe~
 And for my Carat family...
Caranghe~


PS: Sorry for such a long comment...

author: @maymunahuq6238
text:
CARATS we are seen as a lazy fandom, so now we need to show them we aren’t. Vote on Mama, Billboard, Idolchampion, and everything or anything. Also let’s stream Home;Run and semicolon. We said we would get 50 million in just a week, but we haven’t even gotten it to 40 million and it’s been a month. I want the members to see the love and support we have for them, even more than we are showing them. And if possible even stream all the other music videos. We haven’t gotten “very nice” “manse” “adore u” “clap” “fear” “hit” “oh my” or “left and right” at 100 million yet and we said we would. There is so much more mv that I know we can get on top. And let’s even get dwc to 200 million. I know we can do it because I see the huge amount of love the boys get each and every day. Seventeen are the 2nd biggest bg rn, so let’s show everyone else the amazing music and content Seventeen give us.  

Ps. This wasn’t meant to offend anyone in any way. I love so many groups, but I see that Seventeen don’t get the recognized they deserve. And yes I know they got an award recognized by the president of sk, so let’s show everyone why they got the award for changing the culture and arts.

How to stream when you have a wifi?

1. Make a list of what we need to stream.

3. Loop

5. Repeat again.

STREAMING IS EASY WHEN YOU HAVE WIFI. PERIOD. PERIODISM. PERIODIC. PERIODICAL.

author: @shikiynah07
text:
Just finished marathon(ing)XD Just Do It videos like YEAH! So I am 5 days late for this even though BooSeokSoon had been like my top biases from SVT (Boo as my first son) even before they debuted and I'm as hyped as those backup dancers while watching all of those SPECIALs.

Wanted to bring up my mood more so I started scrolling down for comments about how wonderful my children are, but then I stumbled upon some negative and comparison comments.

I knew EXO ever since they debuted but never became my favorite because of the negative vibes I was getting from (some) of their fans. I have friends who feel like that too towards EXO. They wanted to look into the boys but the "fans" are the reason why they don't. Admit it, you can't blame me/us guys. Fans' attitude towards other groups are like a big part of how other people will view their respective favorite groups as well. Why? Because, would you want to be a part of a negative, war freak, and rude family? 'course not. I just hope there will be no so-called Carats out there going around spreading hate. BUT, I TRIED. I IGNORED THOSE SO-CALLED FANS WHO ONLY KNOW HOW TO RUIN THEIR IDOLS' IMAGES AND CONCENTRATED TO EXO'S TALENT. Good thing I tried because for 2 years now, EXO became one of my favorites, too. Especially CBX + Chanyeol and Kai <3 How? I heard CBX on Scarlet Heart Ryeo and I started watching their Showtime and so on.

SVT, on the other hand, debuted 2015 but I knew them first before I came to know EXO. I even watch BSS during SVT TV and Andromeda days so I was sure they were going to be a legit sub-unit one day and my dream finally came true! They worked hard for this. The song, the choreography, and the stages. I was so happy that BSS are even a part of the composition of this song with Woozi.

I really don't know anything about the song some fans here are mentioning so I looked it up and actually HEARD IT and it was nothing like this song apart from the genre and beat and these are common things to have from a lot of different songs not only K-Pop. So, pleeeaaase, stop comparing.

For everyone who's comparing BSS and CBX, please understand this. 

My UB is seungkwan, but I can't deny the similarities. I think since both groups have 3 members and similar vibes, the resemblance is quite evident. BSS might have formed before CBX but we can't argue that CBX debuted first and back at the time, BSS was just SVT gag trio with no asssurance of debut. 

I'm not hating on any groups nor fandoms. Each fandoms have good points on their arguments. Both song are bops, and it'll be better to enjoy them equally as two great songs.

author: @dianamontoya6895
text:
Me parece una excelente canción, y se nota que Woozi la produjo pues está muy bien interpretada. Las voces de Seungkwan y la de DK son asombrosas y Hoshi, como siempre, demostrando sus dotes de baile, más allá de cualquier cosa y supongo que él también puso la coreografía que es muy simpática. Amo a SVT y creo que todo lo que hacen es perfecto. Las comparaciones con la subunidad de EXO son odiosas y no me parece adecuado que se hagan dado que si la SM no ha dicho nada, es porque ya analizó la canción y no existe plagio alguno. El genero es igual, indudablemente, pero la melodía es diferente y no hay que dejarse llevar por las apariencias, porque entonces todas las canciones EDM por ejemplo, serían iguales y no es así, aunque tengan tiempos y ritmos similares. 
Yo no tomo como ofensivo la comparación, si no habla de plagio, porque las voces de SM siempre han destacado por ser excelentes y si los van a comparar, prefiero que sea con ellos, mil veces antes que con otros grupos muy populares pero que no cantan. 
Soy CARAT de corazón y por eso, trato de no buscar problemas con otros fandoms pues quiero que SVT se sienta orgulloso de sus fans que siempre han sido dulces y pacíficas, mucho más que otros fandoms demasiado agresivos y groseros. 
Si a alguien le molesta éste comentario, por favor, una disculpa. No es mi intención molestar a nadie, pero creo que solo digo mi verdad. BESOS PARA TODOS.

author: @afrenchexo-l1418
text:
Being an EXOL myself, I would ask EXOLs who shout "plagiarism" to stop. It's true that there are a lot of similarities with CBX whether it's the concept of suits, choreography or music (I say that with regards to Hey Mama! And Ka-CHING!) but it's not a reason to complain or insult. Everyone is inspired by everyone. The members are different, the lyrics and melodies are different, despite the similarities, the choreography and the MV are different. It's enough to say that it's not plagiarism.

EXO has already been inspired by elders, Big Bang has already been inspired by elders Super Junior has already been inspired by elders, Lady Gaga has already been inspired by elders, David Bowie has already inspired by elders, and last example: Michael Jackson has already been inspired by elders.

I respect Seventeen and the Carats because it is a good group with talented and very nice members, as well for the fandom that I always saw warm. The last thing I want is that there may be tension between our two fandoms while basic we get along well.

Please EXOLs, be mature.
Encourage Seventeen and Carats
Let's focus on the upcoming CBX comeback and be nice.

To Carats, I'm really sorry that some EXOLs have bothered you or could say meanness, I'll try to fix them and educate them as much as possible.
Fighting!
PEACE

The way I see it, the reason why people are saying this song and exo-cbx's ka-ching (both are bops tbh) sound similar is because Hoshi's voice here sounds similar to Xiumin's (and NOT because he's copying him lol). Apart from that, both songs belong to the funk genre (I think?) and, well, there are the suits.
To say that it's a "rip off" is not only not true, but also very disrespectful, inconsiderate and delusional. Before you comment something like that, please take some time to actually think things through.

author: @mazadraniya2066
text:
Listen, to some EXO-Ls that thought it "copied" EXO-CBX concept, here is some information:
1. BSS or Booseoksoon unit is already there since pre-debut, they formed it bcs they are three of the most comedic guys in SVT
2. The song has jazzy-funky style, and yeah, it's the same genre as Ka-ching, but no, it's DOESN'T even has the same melody or key or dance or anything.
3. Suits as stage outfit is common in Kpop, no?
4. Both sub-units are amazingly talented and amazing, both groups are amazing, there is nothing to compare, right?
5. Let's support both groups in peaceful and happy ways 💞

Edit: I did see many comments saying they copied CBX, and this is not for fanwar, just for info. Also, there are so many EXO-Ls that are so kind and supporting towards BooSeokSoon, and we're so thankful, love you EXO-Ls 😁 💕

author: @cherriesforboo6552
text: Reading the comments section makes me realize how gullible some of you can be. If you have not been following SVT's activities then you would obviously complain about how lacklustre this MV is. BOOSEOKSOON is a special unit and they decided to "debut" because this song had such a good response during Carat Land. This is like an informal present for the fans who were waiting for them to come back from Japan. If there was a real MV, they would have hyped it up during their VLive earlier but they did not even mention about any MV. So, this is basically just a small token of appreciation from Pledis. Please lay off the negativity and stop being so hypocritical over small things.

And they did cover their songs like Catallena during trainee days :). So I could see inspiration from OC but with a lot of oringinality and creativity for sure!!! So please do not bury their creativity and originality just bcoz they have same NUMBER of members with some other boygroups.
